LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE SENATE
SENATE BILL NO. 1084
BY RESOURCES AND ENVIRONMENT COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO THE WATER SUPPLY BANK; AMENDING SECTION 42-1764, IDAHO CODE, TO
3 REVISE A PROVISION REGARDING WATER RIGHT FORFEITURE; AND DECLARING AN
4 EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
5 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
6 SECTION 1. That Section 42-1764, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
7 amended to read as follows:
8 42-1764. SUBSTITUTION FOR TRANSFER PROCEEDING -- RIGHTS NOT SUBJECT
9 TO FORFEITURE -- NO DEDICATION OF RIGHTS. (1) The approval of a rental of wa-
10 ter from the water supply bank may be a substitute for the transfer proceed-
11 ing requirements of section 42-222, Idaho Code.
12 (2) Water rights obtained by the board or by a local committee appointed
13 by the board and credited to the water supply bank are not subject to forfei-
14 ture for nonuse pursuant to section 42-222(2), Idaho Code, while retained in
15 or rented from the water supply bank. The five (5) year period of nonuse for
16 forfeiture of a water right shall begin to accrue run anew upon removal of a
17 right from the bank by the owner of the right if a period of nonuse did not oc-
18 cur prior to the date of acceptance of the right into the bank. The five (5)
19 year period of nonuse shall continue to accrue if a period of nonuse occurred
20 prior to the effective date of acceptance of the right into the bank and the
21 right was not beneficially used while in the bank.
22 (3) The rental of water rights from the water supply bank shall not con-
23 stitute a dedication to the lands of any renter since the rental or distri-
24 bution of water by the water bank is only incidental to its primary purposes
25 listed in section 42-1761, Idaho Code.
26 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
27 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
28 July 1, 2025.

